<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430739>
    dc:description "FIGURES 86–97. (86–89). Microsericaria quadripunctata (Brenske, 1896) (Bankura, West Bengal); (90–93). Neoserica quadrilamellata (Brenske, 1896) (West Champaran, Bihar); (94–97). Oxyserica darjeelingia (Brenske, 1898) (West Champaran, Bihar); (86, 90, 94) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (86, 90, 94) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (87, 91, 95) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (88, 92, 96) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430739/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430759>
    dc:description "FIGURE 101. (A–B). A. Gangetic plains biogeographic zone of India; B. Map of Lower Gangetic plains showing sample localities of the species: Maladera sprecherae, M. submucronata, Microsericaria quadripunctata, Neoserica quadrilamellata, Oxyserica darjeelingia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

